whole_object: Looks like someone took "garden variety seating" to a whole new level—this spot is really branching out!
single_object:
- Table: This table is so good at hiding, it's practically "undercover."
- Chairs: Those chairs must be in a band because they really know how to "take a seat."
- Tablecloth: The tablecloth flaunts more patterns than a chameleon at a disco.
- Flowers: These flowers are so bright, they must have graduated "magna bloom laude."
- Statue: The statue stands so still, you'd think it was a professional at "freeze tag."
- Plants: These plants are so popular, they have "fronds" in high places.
- Wall: The wall is so unentertained; it never cracks up.
- Arch: This arch must have studied architecture because it really knows how to "support" a conversation.
- Plates: The plates in this setting are such perfectionists; they're always "dishing out" their best.
- Cups: These cups are so energetic, they always seem to be "mugged" with excitement.
